@startuml seq-first-login
title trawhile — First Login Sequence

actor       "User"                          as User
participant "Browser\n(Angular SPA)"        as Browser
participant "OIDC Provider\n(Google / Apple /\nMicrosoft / Keycloak)" as Provider
participant "Spring Security\n(TrawhileOidcUserService)" as Spring
database    "PostgreSQL"                    as DB

== OIDC callback ==

User   ->  Browser : click "Login with [Provider]"
Browser -> Provider : redirect (OIDC authorise)
User   ->  Provider : authenticate
Provider -> Browser : redirect with authorisation code
Browser -> Spring   : GET /login/oauth2/code/{provider}

Spring -> Provider : exchange code for tokens
note right of Spring
  Decode OIDC ID token → { sub, email, name }
  Apple only: name claim present on first login only;
  absent on subsequent logins.
end note
Provider -> Spring : { subject, email, name }

Spring -> DB : SELECT FROM user_oauth_providers\nWHERE provider = ? AND subject = ?
note right : not found → new user

Spring -> DB : SELECT FROM pending_invitations\nWHERE email = ?

alt no valid invitation (not found or expired)
  Spring -> Browser : redirect /login?error=not_invited
  note right of Spring : SR-C002.F01
else valid invitation

  note right of Spring
    Store { pending_invitations.id, user_id, provider, subject, name }
    in HTTP session. Discard email immediately (UR-C006).
    No DB writes at this point.
    (users row already exists — created at invite time)
    SR-F060.F01
  end note

  Spring -> Browser : redirect → /gdpr-notice

  == GDPR notice ==

  Browser -> Browser : render GDPR notice\n(static content — no auth required)
  User    -> Browser : read & acknowledge

  Browser -> Spring  : POST /auth/gdpr-notice
  Spring  -> Spring  : read pending data from HTTP session
  Spring  -> DB      : BEGIN TRANSACTION
  Spring  -> DB      : INSERT INTO user_profile\n(user_id from session, name from session)
  Spring  -> DB      : INSERT INTO user_oauth_providers\n(provider, subject from session)
  Spring  -> DB      : DELETE FROM pending_invitations\nWHERE id = ? (from session)
  note right of DB
    Bootstrap path only (SR-F001.F01):
    also INSERT INTO users and
    INSERT INTO node_authorizations (admin on root)
  end note
  Spring  -> DB      : COMMIT

  Spring  -> Spring  : establish authenticated session
  Spring  -> Browser : 200 OK { privacyNoticeUrl | null } + session cookie\n(SR-F060.F02)
  note right of Spring
    privacyNoticeUrl is returned only if configured
    and the user has at least one effective
    node authorization after registration.
  end note
  Browser -> Browser : redirect → main application

end

@enduml
